1
00:00:19,397 --> 00:00:20,855
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:25,188
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:27,313 --> 00:00:28,938
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:31,147 --> 00:00:33,063
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:35,313 --> 00:00:37,147
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:42,022 --> 00:00:46,772
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 2)

7
00:00:48,730 --> 00:00:49,980
Here.

8
00:00:52,188 --> 00:00:55,105
This room stinks.

9
00:00:55,813 --> 00:00:56,831
Why did you bring me here?

10
00:00:56,855 --> 00:00:58,438
Didn't you ask me to find you a place?

11
00:00:58,563 --> 00:01:00,063
Don't tell me...

12
00:01:00,188 --> 00:01:01,605
You want me to live here?

13
00:01:02,355 --> 00:01:03,355
That's right.

14
00:01:12,272 --> 00:01:13,772
There's not even a bed...

15
00:01:15,022 --> 00:01:17,105
Or a blanket!

16
00:01:17,230 --> 00:01:20,438
I'm the prince of Blablalis!

17
00:01:21,230 --> 00:01:22,438
Look.

18
00:01:22,563 --> 00:01:25,188
Back in Kauncilion, I had my own bed.

19
00:01:25,313 --> 00:01:27,373
My blanket, everything...
It was all top-of-the-line.

20
00:01:27,397 --> 00:01:30,522
I'm not sleeping here.

21
00:01:33,897 --> 00:01:35,147
Do you hear me?

22
00:01:46,647 --> 00:01:47,688
"Proof"

23
00:01:48,272 --> 00:01:50,563
I don't even know if I'm doing a good job.

24
00:01:52,188 --> 00:01:55,772
Hiring a rookie like this...

25
00:01:56,230 --> 00:01:57,022
What is going on?

26
00:01:57,147 --> 00:01:58,563
I should just call the police.

27
00:01:58,688 --> 00:02:01,147
Boss, please give me a chance.

28
00:02:01,272 --> 00:02:03,438
I'm great at baking bread.

29
00:02:04,563 --> 00:02:05,272
Let go!

30
00:02:05,397 --> 00:02:06,605
Boss.

31
00:02:09,938 --> 00:02:10,938
Boss...

32
00:02:11,063 --> 00:02:12,272
This is driving me crazy.

33
00:02:15,022 --> 00:02:17,605
Wooju, can you open the door?

34
00:02:19,272 --> 00:02:20,397
Hyung.

35
00:02:20,897 --> 00:02:22,730
Why'd you show up without calling?

36
00:02:22,855 --> 00:02:25,397
Since when do I need to call ahead?

37
00:02:26,522 --> 00:02:27,980
I was worried, so I came by.

38
00:02:28,105 --> 00:02:29,313
But...

39
00:02:29,438 --> 00:02:31,647
Looks like you've pretty
much got things in order.

40
00:02:33,188 --> 00:02:35,397
I've cleaned everything up.

41
00:02:37,397 --> 00:02:39,355
But who's this guy?

42
00:02:39,730 --> 00:02:40,772
He's a part-timer.

43
00:02:40,897 --> 00:02:42,397
A part-timer?

44
00:02:42,522 --> 00:02:44,206
He's an international
student from Thailand.

45
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:46,164
I heard his family is
going through a tough time.

46
00:02:46,188 --> 00:02:47,548
My family isn't struggling at all.

47
00:02:47,605 --> 00:02:48,355
I'm royalty.

48
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:49,480
His family went bankrupt.

49
00:02:49,605 --> 00:02:53,480
He sold his house just to come here.

50
00:02:53,605 --> 00:02:57,730
And now he only has 150,000 won left.

51
00:02:59,105 --> 00:03:02,355
But it seems like this
guy understands Korean.

52
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:08,063
Yeah. So, what part of the Thai
countryside are you from?

53
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:09,331
I'm not from the countryside.

54
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:11,063
I'm from the capital, a big city, okay?

55
00:03:11,188 --> 00:03:15,813
Alright. Please take good care of
Wooju Bakery and its owner.

56
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:19,022
I'm Woo-hyuk.

57
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:29,605
I'm Raon.

58
00:03:29,730 --> 00:03:32,397
Don't worry. I'm great at baking.

59
00:03:32,772 --> 00:03:33,855
That's enough.

60
00:03:34,272 --> 00:03:35,272
Come here.

61
00:03:35,313 --> 00:03:36,022
Hyung.

62
00:03:36,147 --> 00:03:37,730
What's gotten into you today?

63
00:03:37,855 --> 00:03:38,438
Just come here.

64
00:03:38,563 --> 00:03:39,938
Jeez.

65
00:03:51,105 --> 00:03:53,272
Raon, go get yourself settled.

66
00:03:54,230 --> 00:03:55,772
Want to bake some bread?

67
00:03:55,897 --> 00:03:57,730
You're the one who broke the oven.

68
00:03:57,855 --> 00:03:59,022
We can just fix it.

69
00:03:59,147 --> 00:04:03,563
You couldn't even fix
the car you came in...

70
00:04:15,813 --> 00:04:19,397
Hey, the most important part is broken.

71
00:04:21,313 --> 00:04:23,938
Hachi, can you give me a hand?

72
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,522
(Wooju Bakery)

73
00:05:19,355 --> 00:05:21,355
Boss, what are you thinking about?

74
00:05:26,522 --> 00:05:28,605
Just thinking about when I was a kid.

75
00:05:29,772 --> 00:05:30,563
Is that so?

76
00:05:30,688 --> 00:05:33,248
I thought you were upset because
the bread didn't turn out well.

77
00:05:34,105 --> 00:05:36,813
What? I'm an amazing baker.

78
00:05:44,730 --> 00:05:46,022
Watch.

79
00:05:48,147 --> 00:05:49,789
When you're kneading dough,
you have to think happy thoughts.

80
00:05:49,813 --> 00:05:51,688
Don't think about sad things...

81
00:05:53,605 --> 00:05:54,230
Why?

82
00:05:54,355 --> 00:05:56,272
Because even our fingertips...

83
00:05:56,397 --> 00:05:58,772
transfer our emotions into the dough.

84
00:05:59,438 --> 00:06:02,355
When customers eat the bread,
they can feel it too.

85
00:06:08,647 --> 00:06:10,230
I...

86
00:06:13,772 --> 00:06:16,897
don't have many happy memories.

87
00:06:18,313 --> 00:06:23,397
Then try to think of one.

88
00:07:05,188 --> 00:07:08,522
Wow, you can see the whole city from here.

89
00:07:12,730 --> 00:07:16,105
When I'm feeling down, I
come here with my hyung.

90
00:07:17,105 --> 00:07:20,605
My parents passed away when I was five.

91
00:07:20,730 --> 00:07:26,855
So I met my hyung at an orphanage.

92
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:28,397
That must have been tough.

93
00:07:29,313 --> 00:07:30,188
Not really.

94
00:07:30,313 --> 00:07:32,563
Thanks to my hyung, I managed.

95
00:07:33,022 --> 00:07:34,331
Besides, I had a dream back then.

96
00:07:34,355 --> 00:07:35,105
What dream?

97
00:07:35,230 --> 00:07:36,730
To open a bakery and be the owner.

98
00:07:36,855 --> 00:07:38,438
So where did you learn to bake?

99
00:07:38,563 --> 00:07:40,438
At a baking school.

100
00:07:41,022 --> 00:07:42,772
But...

101
00:07:43,022 --> 00:07:44,914
You're trying to say my
bread tastes bad, aren't you?

102
00:07:44,938 --> 00:07:48,980
It's because of long COVID.
I lost my sense of taste.

103
00:07:49,438 --> 00:07:50,063
That's terrible.

104
00:07:50,188 --> 00:07:52,772
The doctor said it'll come back soon.

105
00:07:52,897 --> 00:07:54,313
Once my sense of taste returns...

106
00:07:54,438 --> 00:07:56,373
I'm going to make bread
that's as delicious as my dad's.

107
00:07:56,397 --> 00:07:57,772
Your dad was a baker too?

108
00:07:57,897 --> 00:08:00,688
Yeah. You know Wooju Bakery, right?

109
00:08:00,813 --> 00:08:04,647
My parents used to run their bakery there.

110
00:08:04,772 --> 00:08:05,980
Really?

111
00:08:07,188 --> 00:08:09,230
The bread my dad made...

112
00:08:09,772 --> 00:08:12,147
was really special.

113
00:08:12,272 --> 00:08:16,605
I loved the star-shaped bread the most.

114
00:08:19,855 --> 00:08:22,397
I've never tried your dad's bread...

115
00:08:22,647 --> 00:08:24,647
but I'm sure it was delicious.

116
00:08:24,772 --> 00:08:26,022
How do you know?

117
00:08:32,897 --> 00:08:37,688
Because I can feel the taste from
your memories in my hands right now.

118
00:08:45,980 --> 00:08:50,563
Hey, that's the kind of
line people use to flirt.

119
00:08:55,980 --> 00:08:58,022
What does your name, "Wooju," mean?

120
00:09:00,188 --> 00:09:03,855
"Space, the universe."
My mom gave me that name.

121
00:09:05,397 --> 00:09:07,063
It's a beautiful name.

122
00:09:16,093 --> 00:09:17,843
Prince, want to try?

123
00:09:18,063 --> 00:09:20,813
I promise you, that one is so good.

124
00:09:32,313 --> 00:09:33,414
This is good enough to sell.

125
00:09:33,438 --> 00:09:35,605
Right? I told you.

126
00:09:35,789 --> 00:09:37,211
Give it here. Thanks.

127
00:10:25,855 --> 00:10:27,897
Hello, everyone.

128
00:10:28,022 --> 00:10:31,897
Today, I'm at a bakery in Namyangju.

129
00:10:32,022 --> 00:10:36,230
This place is called "Wooju Bakery."

130
00:10:36,772 --> 00:10:40,522
First off, the staff here
has a terrible attitude.

131
00:10:40,855 --> 00:10:42,998
A customer walked in, and
they didn't even look at me.

132
00:10:43,022 --> 00:10:46,355
Excuse me, can you recommend
your most popular item?

133
00:10:48,438 --> 00:10:49,730
Poop and pee.

134
00:10:49,855 --> 00:10:51,855
I'm a YouTuber with a million subscribers.

135
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:54,272
I'm here to promote your
place, so I won't be paying.

136
00:10:54,397 --> 00:10:55,980
In fact, you should be paying me.

137
00:10:56,105 --> 00:10:58,225
I'll just consider this me
doing you a favor, got it?

138
00:10:59,563 --> 00:11:00,897
No freebies.

139
00:11:01,022 --> 00:11:02,272
Pay first.

140
00:11:09,105 --> 00:11:13,022
This looks like coffee with whipped cream.

141
00:11:17,438 --> 00:11:18,688
How could you...

142
00:11:19,272 --> 00:11:20,272
What the heck is this?

143
00:11:20,341 --> 00:11:20,883
Why?

144
00:11:21,022 --> 00:11:22,938
This isn't coke, and it's not coffee.

145
00:11:23,063 --> 00:11:25,105
And that on top doesn't
look like whipped cream.

146
00:11:25,230 --> 00:11:27,147
It kind of looks like mayonnaise.

147
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:31,105
What is this drink called?

148
00:11:32,063 --> 00:11:33,355
That's "Space Pee."

149
00:11:34,688 --> 00:11:37,397
Well, I'll try the bread then.

150
00:11:41,022 --> 00:11:42,647
Huh?

151
00:11:42,772 --> 00:11:43,772
This taste...

152
00:11:43,813 --> 00:11:46,605
This bread is called "I Miss You."

153
00:11:46,730 --> 00:11:47,730
This taste...

154
00:11:47,813 --> 00:11:51,647
Doesn't it make you cry
when you think of that person?

155
00:11:51,772 --> 00:11:52,980
What is this?

156
00:11:53,105 --> 00:11:54,147
Ah, it's so spicy!

157
00:11:54,272 --> 00:11:58,355
Seriously, what the heck?
Why is the bread spicy?

158
00:11:58,813 --> 00:12:01,480
Everyone, this bakery
is absolutely terrible.

159
00:12:01,605 --> 00:12:03,147
What is this place even doing, huh?

160
00:12:03,272 --> 00:12:06,480
They put mayonnaise in their drinks
and wasabi in their bread!

161
00:12:06,605 --> 00:12:09,022
Everyone, do not come to this place.

162
00:12:09,688 --> 00:12:11,188
Are you curious?

163
00:12:11,313 --> 00:12:13,980
Don't even be curious. Just stay away.

164
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:21,438
Boss, wake up.

165
00:12:32,397 --> 00:12:34,063
Boss, get up.

166
00:12:37,647 --> 00:12:38,938
Boss.

167
00:12:40,813 --> 00:12:41,956
What the heck are you doing, you psycho?

168
00:12:41,980 --> 00:12:43,230
I'm not the psycho.

169
00:12:43,688 --> 00:12:46,768
The boss who's still sleeping after
opening hours is the one with the problem.

170
00:12:48,022 --> 00:12:50,063
What? It's already past nine?

171
00:12:50,188 --> 00:12:51,855
Don't worry, the shop is already open.

172
00:12:51,980 --> 00:12:53,355
You said the shop is open?

173
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,647
So what if it's open?

174
00:12:54,772 --> 00:12:58,147
To do business, you need bread at least.

175
00:12:58,272 --> 00:12:59,105
I've already made the bread.

176
00:12:59,230 --> 00:13:00,230
You know how to bake?

177
00:13:00,272 --> 00:13:03,105
I learned from the best
baker in the universe.

178
00:13:10,230 --> 00:13:11,230
Move.

179
00:13:13,688 --> 00:13:16,938
I'm sorry, it seems we're
having some issues today.

180
00:13:17,063 --> 00:13:18,272
We're not having any issues.

181
00:13:19,313 --> 00:13:21,355
This is a cosmic level of deliciousness.

182
00:13:22,022 --> 00:13:25,688
Keep your voice down!
We're in front of a customer.

183
00:13:28,563 --> 00:13:30,163
This person doesn't count as a customer.

184
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:35,897
This is unbelievable.

185
00:13:36,022 --> 00:13:36,855
Did you all see that?

186
00:13:36,980 --> 00:13:39,022
At least the owner has some sense.

187
00:13:39,147 --> 00:13:42,772
But the employee is completely shameless.

188
00:13:42,897 --> 00:13:44,730
Have you ever baked before?

189
00:13:44,855 --> 00:13:48,355
I can use a translator,
so you can speak Thai.

190
00:13:49,397 --> 00:13:51,355
I'm not a professional baker.

191
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,522
But I am a prince.

192
00:13:52,647 --> 00:13:55,127
And I grew up eating the most
delicious bread in the universe.

193
00:13:57,897 --> 00:13:59,147
Watch your attitude.

194
00:13:59,855 --> 00:14:03,438
He has the nerve to call himself a prince.

195
00:14:04,438 --> 00:14:07,272
But why would a prince be here?

196
00:14:08,272 --> 00:14:10,647
I ran away because I was
being forced into a marriage.

197
00:14:11,438 --> 00:14:16,397
I needed some time to figure things out.

198
00:14:19,063 --> 00:14:23,272
So you ran away from your fiancée?
How shameless.

199
00:14:26,063 --> 00:14:29,480
What is that? A person or a dog? (Used the rude version of "person")

200
00:14:31,147 --> 00:14:32,313
Hachi.

201
00:14:34,688 --> 00:14:36,188
What did you just say?

202
00:14:36,313 --> 00:14:37,438
Hachi.

203
00:14:37,855 --> 00:14:38,980
Hachi.

204
00:14:40,605 --> 00:14:46,063
What are you doing?
Ugh, you stink! Get away.

205
00:14:46,188 --> 00:14:48,563
Don't touch me! This is so annoying.

206
00:14:48,688 --> 00:14:49,480
You're messing up my hair.

207
00:14:49,605 --> 00:14:51,188
Don't touch me!

208
00:14:53,022 --> 00:14:55,813
Let go! I said, let go!

209
00:14:58,688 --> 00:15:00,355
Do you have any idea what you did wrong?

210
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:02,480
You were sleeping.

211
00:15:03,022 --> 00:15:03,855
The store needs to stay open.

212
00:15:03,980 --> 00:15:05,397
We made the bread and drinks.

213
00:15:05,522 --> 00:15:06,397
Is there anything wrong with that?

214
00:15:06,522 --> 00:15:08,105
You call this bread and drinks?

215
00:15:09,105 --> 00:15:10,539
The least you could do
is make something edible.

216
00:15:10,563 --> 00:15:12,498
A YouTuber with millions of
subscribers visited our shop.

217
00:15:12,522 --> 00:15:14,938
If word gets out that
we're a terrible bakery,

218
00:15:15,063 --> 00:15:17,498
we're finished. We'll go bankrupt.
We're seriously going to go bankrupt!

219
00:15:17,522 --> 00:15:19,522
But it's your fault for hiring us.

220
00:15:19,897 --> 00:15:21,980
So what? Did I ever
say I wanted to hire you?

221
00:15:22,105 --> 00:15:23,438
And why did you suddenly bite me?

222
00:15:23,563 --> 00:15:25,730
What are you, a dog?
You actually are a dog!

223
00:15:25,855 --> 00:15:27,272
Did you even taste that bread?

224
00:15:27,938 --> 00:15:31,480
Why are you taking that crazy woman's
word for it and giving us a hard time?

225
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:33,105
Go on, try it yourself.

226
00:15:35,188 --> 00:15:37,397
What on earth are these ingredients?

227
00:15:38,355 --> 00:15:40,022
Wasabi... and mayonnaise...

228
00:15:40,147 --> 00:15:41,605
I would never put wasabi in bread.

229
00:15:41,730 --> 00:15:43,530
And I wouldn't just
dump pepper in like this.

230
00:15:47,813 --> 00:15:49,272
I can tell without even tasting it.

231
00:16:15,647 --> 00:16:17,407
What's happening? Is
my sense of taste back?

232
00:16:19,813 --> 00:16:21,331
(Songcheon Chinese Cuisine)
Tell me about it.

233
00:16:21,355 --> 00:16:23,522
That place is definitely gonna fail for real.

234
00:16:23,647 --> 00:16:26,272
That bakery was the absolute worst.

235
00:16:26,397 --> 00:16:29,730
Even the name "Wooju Bakery" is so lame.

236
00:16:29,855 --> 00:16:31,897
The response to my video has been amazing.

237
00:16:32,022 --> 00:16:36,272
Oh, and the staff there?
They're a bunch of total weirdos.

238
00:16:36,397 --> 00:16:39,355
They're basically some kind of alien.

239
00:16:40,355 --> 00:16:42,605
So, when do I get the rest of my payment?

240
00:16:51,605 --> 00:16:53,063
You scared me.

241
00:16:53,188 --> 00:16:55,938
What, are you interested in me?

242
00:16:56,063 --> 00:16:57,873
I'm a YouTuber with millions
of subscribers, you know.

243
00:16:57,897 --> 00:17:02,563
I'm not the kind of girl who
just meets up with any guy.

244
00:17:04,897 --> 00:17:08,730
Why are you so determined
to ruin Wooju Bakery?

245
00:17:08,855 --> 00:17:10,980
I have millions of subscribers, okay?

246
00:17:11,105 --> 00:17:13,480
Taking that place down
is a piece of cake for me.

247
00:17:15,355 --> 00:17:21,105
What makes you think
the people working there are like aliens?

248
00:17:22,938 --> 00:17:27,688
What kind of normal person would make that
kind of bread and those kinds of drinks?

249
00:17:27,813 --> 00:17:29,355
Besides, if they were human,

250
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:31,480
why would they take my beautiful fingers

251
00:17:31,605 --> 00:17:33,105
and just bite them?

252
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:35,813
So what are you planning to do next?

253
00:17:36,188 --> 00:17:38,480
I'm going to film a second video.

254
00:17:38,897 --> 00:17:41,938
I'll expose those aliens
for who they really are.

255
00:17:44,065 --> 00:17:46,025
What do you plan to
do by dragging her here?

256
00:17:46,147 --> 00:17:49,355
The fact that Prince Kauncilion
is an alien has already been exposed.

257
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:52,272
If we're not careful, he could
be captured by Earthlings.

258
00:17:52,397 --> 00:17:54,938
He might even end up being dissected.

259
00:17:55,063 --> 00:17:58,938
If that happens, we'll
have no way to escape.

260
00:17:59,063 --> 00:18:02,313
We could be stuck here for a hundred years,
or even two hundred.

261
00:18:05,605 --> 00:18:08,230
Hyung, this is incredible.

262
00:18:08,305 --> 00:18:11,022
They made this. Try it.

263
00:18:15,147 --> 00:18:16,522
Well? What do you think?

264
00:18:19,438 --> 00:18:22,355
It doesn't taste like bread, right?

265
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,938
Is this Thai food?

266
00:18:24,063 --> 00:18:27,855
Raon, I've never tasted anything like this.
Do you have a recipe?

267
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:29,313
This is unbelievably good.

268
00:18:30,313 --> 00:18:34,272
I have taste buds on my hands.

269
00:18:40,063 --> 00:18:41,897
You see all those ingredients over there?

270
00:18:42,397 --> 00:18:45,313
I taste with my hands
and create from there.

271
00:18:45,438 --> 00:18:50,022
You can taste with your hands?

272
00:18:50,522 --> 00:18:52,397
So you just winged it without a recipe?

273
00:18:52,730 --> 00:18:55,230
Usually, food are made like that.

274
00:18:55,355 --> 00:18:56,355
That's not what I meant.

275
00:18:56,397 --> 00:18:57,563
I mean it literally.

276
00:18:57,688 --> 00:18:59,897
I really do have taste buds on my hands.

277
00:19:01,147 --> 00:19:03,313
Dude, they're completely insane.

278
00:19:03,438 --> 00:19:05,498
A huge influencer with millions
of subscribers came by today.

279
00:19:05,522 --> 00:19:06,938
And they totally screwed up.

280
00:19:07,355 --> 00:19:10,063
I think she was live streaming.

281
00:19:10,188 --> 00:19:12,272
She said she's never coming back.

282
00:19:12,397 --> 00:19:13,748
I guess we can forget
about having any customers...

283
00:19:13,772 --> 00:19:17,438
It's okay. We'll start by turning
the neighbors into regulars.

284
00:19:17,563 --> 00:19:18,748
Then we'll slowly build
up our customer base.

285
00:19:18,772 --> 00:19:20,063
Hmm?

286
00:19:21,272 --> 00:19:22,480
I know you can do it.

287
00:19:23,980 --> 00:19:28,105
Are you two... also engaged?

288
00:19:28,355 --> 00:19:33,147
What, do we look like a couple who love each other?

289
00:19:33,813 --> 00:19:34,605
Yeah.

290
00:19:34,730 --> 00:19:37,272
We're just good friends.

291
00:19:39,105 --> 00:19:40,688
Really close friends.

292
00:19:42,063 --> 00:19:43,438
I thought you two were engaged.

293
00:19:43,563 --> 00:19:46,480
Like you were in a relationship.

294
00:19:48,063 --> 00:19:49,688
If you have feelings for each other,

295
00:19:50,063 --> 00:19:52,188
does that mean you're
dating or even engaged?

296
00:19:52,313 --> 00:19:53,313
Well, not necessarily...

297
00:19:53,355 --> 00:19:54,647
Actually, I have a fiancée too.

298
00:19:54,772 --> 00:19:56,438
But we're not together because of love.

299
00:19:57,813 --> 00:20:01,147
He left his fiancée back home
and just took off.

300
00:20:01,688 --> 00:20:02,980
What was it called...

301
00:20:03,105 --> 00:20:06,147
To get out of an arranged
political marriage, he said.

302
00:20:08,105 --> 00:20:10,605
An arranged marriage?
Everyone knows about those.

303
00:20:10,730 --> 00:20:13,688
That's something only rich families do.

304
00:20:13,813 --> 00:20:15,063
I...

305
00:20:17,397 --> 00:20:17,980
Prince...

306
00:20:18,105 --> 00:20:20,272
I feel them... they're coming!

307
00:20:20,397 --> 00:20:21,688
Who's here?

308
00:20:35,313 --> 00:20:37,730
Princess, come in.

309
00:21:10,313 --> 00:21:12,772
I thought you'd fled to
the ends of the universe.

310
00:21:12,897 --> 00:21:14,438
But you only made it to Earth?

311
00:21:21,105 --> 00:21:23,022
Your Highness, you've had a long journey.

312
00:21:23,563 --> 00:21:25,397
Coming all this way yourself.

313
00:21:25,688 --> 00:21:26,813
Save it.

314
00:21:27,563 --> 00:21:29,147
Why did you run away?

315
00:21:29,272 --> 00:21:30,772
Do you have any idea

316
00:21:30,897 --> 00:21:33,522
what a mess our country is in
now that you've disappeared?

317
00:21:33,647 --> 00:21:35,022
But...

318
00:21:35,272 --> 00:21:37,022
How did you know I ran away to this place?

319
00:21:37,147 --> 00:21:39,897
I removed the listening
device from that little dog's ear.

320
00:21:44,022 --> 00:21:45,188
But...

321
00:21:45,313 --> 00:21:47,313
I didn't run away because I hate you.

322
00:21:47,980 --> 00:21:49,438
Is that so?

323
00:21:52,980 --> 00:21:54,647
But I hate you.

324
00:21:55,272 --> 00:21:57,022
You're not my type at all.

325
00:21:57,147 --> 00:21:58,355
Huh?

326
00:21:58,480 --> 00:22:00,480
I hate arranged marriages too.

327
00:22:01,397 --> 00:22:04,313
Then why did you come all the way here?

328
00:22:07,355 --> 00:22:09,188
If I bring you back,

329
00:22:09,313 --> 00:22:11,730
our engagement will be called off.

330
00:22:11,855 --> 00:22:14,313
Your father promised me himself.

331
00:22:16,105 --> 00:22:17,355
Is it this guy?

332
00:22:18,855 --> 00:22:20,063
Is it him?

333
00:22:20,188 --> 00:22:21,813
Your Highness?

334
00:22:23,022 --> 00:22:24,938
Wait, how can a princess be a guy?

335
00:22:25,063 --> 00:22:27,772
If you're handsome, you're a prince.

336
00:22:27,897 --> 00:22:29,289
If you're beautiful, you're a princess.

337
00:22:29,313 --> 00:22:31,105
Are you hitting on me right now?

338
00:22:31,230 --> 00:22:32,980
There are no women in space.

339
00:22:33,105 --> 00:22:35,813
The concept of gender only exists on Earth.

340
00:22:37,980 --> 00:22:40,355
The way I see it...

341
00:22:42,897 --> 00:22:44,647
You must be a prince then, Your Highness.

342
00:22:45,522 --> 00:22:47,480
Hey, change of plans.

343
00:22:48,105 --> 00:22:49,873
Let's stick around and have
some fun on Earth before we go.

344
00:22:49,897 --> 00:22:51,147
Why?

345
00:22:51,897 --> 00:22:53,438
How should I put this...

346
00:22:54,605 --> 00:22:58,688
It's not easy to find love in space.

347
00:23:00,813 --> 00:23:02,105
Let's go.

348
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:03,772
He's insane!

349
00:24:38,563 --> 00:24:40,313
Damn it.

350
00:24:47,063 --> 00:24:48,480
What are these guys talking about?

351
00:24:48,605 --> 00:24:49,438
Aliens?

352
00:24:49,563 --> 00:24:50,938
Wooju Bakery?

353
00:24:52,022 --> 00:24:53,397
You're all so dead!
